data.chText: 由某事引起
data.enText: caused by sth

data.chText: 后果；结果
data.enText: a thing that is caused or produced because of sth else

data.chText: 她由于受伤而死亡。
data.enText: She died as a result of her injuries.

data.chText: 公司倒闭的直接原因是经营不善。
data.enText: The failure of the company was a direct result of bad management.

data.chText: 他犯了个大错，结果丢了工作。
data.enText: He made one big mistake, and, as a result, lost his job.

data.chText: 农场被淹，收成损失了一大半。
data.enText: The farm was flooded, with the result that most of the harvest was lost.

data.chText: 她勤奋苦读，终于进了医学院。
data.enText: The end result (= the final one) of her hard work was a place at medical school.

data.chText: 这本书是25年研究的结晶。
data.enText: This book is the result of 25 years of research.

data.chText: 比赛；选举
data.enText: of game/election

data.chText: 结果（包括比分、得票、获胜者或当选者名单等）
data.enText: the final score or the name of the winner in a sports event, competition, election, etc.

data.chText: 今晚他们将宣布投票结果。
data.enText: They will announce the result of the vote tonight.

data.chText: 选举结果
data.enText: the election results

data.chText: 足球比赛的结果
data.enText: the football results

data.chText: （尤指足球比赛的）胜利，胜局
data.enText: a victory or a success, especially in a game of football ( soccer )

data.chText: 这场比赛我们非赢不可。
data.enText: We badly need to get a result from this match.

data.chText: 考试
data.enText: of exam

data.chText: 得分；成绩
data.enText: the mark/grade you get in an exam or in a number of exams

data.chText: 你知道考试成绩了吗？
data.enText: Have you had your results yet?

data.chText: 测试；研究
data.enText: of test/research

data.chText: 结果；成果
data.enText: the information that you get from a scientific test or piece of research

data.chText: 实验结果
data.enText: the result of an experiment

data.chText: 成功
data.enText: success

data.chText: 成功实现的事；成果；成效
data.enText: things that are achieved successfully

data.chText: 这项工程开始显出成效。
data.enText: The project is beginning to show results.

data.chText: 善于调动队员获取成功的教练
data.enText: a coach who knows how to get results from his players

data.chText: （因…）发生；（随…）产生
data.enText: to happen because of sth else that happened first

data.chText: 生产革新造成的失业
data.enText: job losses resulting from changes in production

data.chText: 水位上升，就会发生洪水。
data.enText: When water levels rise, flooding results.

data.chText: 爆炸相当剧烈，造成的破坏范围很大。
data.enText: It was a large explosion and the resulting damage was extensive.
result in sth

data.chText: 造成；导致
data.enText: to make sth happen

data.chText: 气旋已经造成了成千上万的人死亡。
data.enText: The cyclone has resulted in many thousands of deaths.

data.chText: 这些政策使得许多老人饱受困苦。
data.enText: These policies resulted in many elderly people suffering hardship.

data.chText: 以上各词均表示结果。
data.enText: These are all words for a thing that is caused because of sth else.
effect

data.chText: 指对人 / 事产生的效应、影响、结果：
data.enText: a change in sb/sth that is caused by sb/sth else

data.chText: 她的批评使他完全丧失了信心。
data.enText: Her criticisms had the effect of discouraging him completely.
result

data.chText: 指后果、结果：
data.enText: a thing that is caused or produced by sth else

data.chText: 她由于受伤而死亡。
data.enText: She died as a result of her injuries.

data.chText: 这本书是25年研究的结晶。
data.enText: This book is the result of 25 years of research.
consequence

data.chText: 尤指不好的结果、后果：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) a result of sth that has happened, especially a bad result

data.chText: 这项决定可能会对该行业产生严重后果。
data.enText: This decision could have serious consequences for the industry.

data.chText: consequence最常用以指可能产生的负面结果，常与adverse、dire、disastrous、fatal、harmful、negative、serious、tragic、unfortunate等词连用。即使没有形容词修饰，consequence也常含负面结果之意。
data.enText: Consequences is used most frequently to talk about possible negative results of an action. It is commonly used with such words as adverse , dire , disastrous , fatal , harmful , negative , serious , tragic and unfortunate . Even when there is no adjective, consequences often suggests negative results.
outcome

data.chText: 指行动或过程的结果、效果：
data.enText: the result of an action or process

data.chText: 我们在等待谈判的最终结果。
data.enText: We are waiting to hear the final outcome of the negotiations.

data.chText: 用result还是outcome？
result常指直接引致的结果：
data.enText: Result is often used to talk about things that are caused directly by sth else.

data.chText: 好斗情绪通常是害怕所致。
data.enText: Aggression is often the result of fear.

data.chText: outcome较常指某一过程完结时的结果，原因和结果之间的关系已不太明显：
data.enText: Outcome is more often used to talk about what happens at the end of a process when the exact relation of cause and effect is less clear.
Aggresssion is often the outcome of fear.

data.chText: result常用于事情过去之后的结果，outcome常用于谈及行动或过程可能会产生的结果。
data.enText: Result is often used after an event to talk about what happened. Outcome is often used before an action or process to talk about what is likely to happen.
result or outcome?
repercussion

data.chText: 指行动或事情过去之后可能产生的间接而常为负面的影响、反响
data.enText: ( rather formal ) an indirect and usually bad result of an action or event that may happen some time afterwards
to have consequences/repercussions for sb/sth
with the effect/result/consequence/outcome that…
a(n)/the possible/likely/inevitable effect/result/consequences/outcome/repercussions
(a/an) dramatic/far-reaching/serious/negative effect/results/consequences/outcome/repercussions
(a) lasting effect/result/consequences/repercussions
the final result/outcome
the end result
to have an effect/a result/consequences/an outcome/repercussions
to achieve/get/obtain a(n) effect/result/outcome

simple_means.memory_skill: re 回 + sult 跳 → 跳回来的东西 → 结果

means: 结果(包括比分、得票、获胜者或当选者名单等)

ex.chText: 战争过后生活变得更加艰难。
ex.enText: Life became even harder in the aftermath of the war.

ex.chText: 已采取措施预防地震后引发疫病。
ex.enText: Measures were taken to prevent the disease in the aftermath of the earthquake.

synonyms.bx: 强调灾难（如风暴、地震、战争等）留下的后果。

ex.chText: 你考虑过失败的后果吗？
ex.enText: Have you considered the consequences of your failure?

ex.chText: 谁来承担战争的后果？
ex.enText: Who will shoulder the consequences of the war?

synonyms.bx: 强调逻辑关系，多指不良结果。

ex.chText: 这场战争的结局就是敌人无条件投降。
ex.enText: The outcome of the war is the unconditional surrender of the enemy.

ex.chText: 大选的结果无法预测。
ex.enText: It's impossible to predict the outcome of the general election.

synonyms.bx: 侧重指预先不知道的结果。

ex.chText: 他的病是由饮用受污染的水引起的。
ex.enText: His illness is the result of drinking polluted water.

ex.chText: 不同物种的进化是自然选择的结果。
ex.enText: The development of different species is the result of natural selection.

ex.chText: 由于雾太大，所有航班都延误了。
ex.enText: As a result of the heavy fog, all flights have been delayed.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，强调因为某事而引起的结果。

ex.chText: 比赛离终场还有两分钟时，双方比分为5比0。
ex.enText: The score was five-nil with two minutes left in the game.

ex.chText: 他阅读测验的成绩很令人失望。
ex.enText: His score on the reading test was very disappointing.

ex.chText: 这男孩的智商为126分。
ex.enText: The boy had an IQ score of 126.

synonyms.bx: 指运动、比赛、考试、科学测验等的得分。

ex.chText: 他英语得了一个Ａ，老师感到很惊讶。
ex.enText: The teacher was surprised that he got a grade A in English.

ex.chText: 她努力学习，取得了好成绩。
ex.enText: She worked hard and got good grades.

synonyms.bx: 指学习或考试成绩，通常用字母而非数字表示。

ex.chText: 我化学得了个B。
ex.enText: My mark in chemistry is B.

ex.chText: 她这学期的成绩略有提高。
ex.enText: Her marks have been a bit higher this term.

ex.chText: 他期终考试得了满分。
ex.enText: He got full marks on the final examination.

ex.chText: 及格分数是(百分制)60分。
ex.enText: The pass mark was 60%.

synonyms.bx: 尤指老师给学生的分数、成绩。

ex.chText: 他落后领先者2分。
ex.enText: He is two points behind the leader.

ex.chText: 如果你不能准时完成字谜就扣1分。
ex.enText: You lose a point if you can't complete the puzzle on time.

ex.chText: 他英语测验得了95分。
ex.enText: He got 95 points in the English test.

synonyms.bx: 主要指运动、比赛中的得分，有时也指考试的分数。

ex.chText: 你知道你的考试成绩吗？
ex.enText: Do you know your exam results?

ex.chText: 足球比赛的结果将在午夜公布。
ex.enText: The football results will be announced at midnight.

synonyms.bx: 指比赛的最终结果，或某一门考试的得分。

ex.chText: 她在今天的比赛中获得了创纪录的比分。
ex.enText: She made a record tally at today's game.

ex.chText: 目前英格兰队的积分是9分，苏格兰队是7分。
ex.enText: England's tally at the moment is 9 points, against Scotland's 7.

synonyms.bx: 指比赛等活动中到某一时间段的得分或积分。

data.enText: result in sth

data.chText: 造成；导致
data.enText: to make sth happen

data.chText: 气旋已经造成了成千上万的人死亡。
data.enText: The cyclone has resulted in many thousands of deaths.

data.chText: 这些政策使得许多老人饱受困苦。
data.enText: These policies resulted in many elderly people suffering hardship.

tr: the semantic role of the noun phrase whose referent exists only by virtue of the activity denoted by the verb in the clause
a statement that solves a problem or explains how to solve the problem
example: they were trying to find a peaceful solution
the answers were in the back of the book
he computed the result to four decimal places
he listened for the results on the radio

tr: a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon
example: the magnetic effect was greater when the rod was lengthwise
his decision had depressing consequences for business
he acted very wise after the event

tr: come about or follow as a consequence
example: nothing will result from this meeting

tr: issue or terminate (in a specified way, state, etc.)
have as a result or residue
example: The water left a mark on the silk dress
Her blood left a stain on the napkin

value.def: A result is something that happens or exists because of something else that has happened.

example.ex: Compensation is available for people who have developed asthma as a direct result of their work...
example.tran: 直接因工作原因患上哮喘的人会获得赔偿。

example.ex: A real pizza oven gives better results than an ordinary home oven.
example.tran: 专门的比萨烤箱比普通家用烤箱效果更好。

value.def: If something results in a particular situation or event, it causes that situation or event to happen.

example.ex: Fifty per cent of road accidents result in head injuries...
example.tran: 50％的道路交通事故都会导致头部损伤。

example.ex: Regular trips back to her adopted motherland have resulted in her first book, Tiger Balm.
example.tran: 经常返回她移居的国家让她写出了她的第一本书《万金油》。

value.def: If something results from a particular event or action, it is caused by that event or action.

example.ex: Many hair problems result from what you eat...
example.tran: 很多头发问题都是由饮食引起的。

example.ex: Ignore the early warnings and illness could result.
example.tran: 忽略早期征兆可能会导致疾病。

value.def: A result is the situation that exists at the end of a contest.

example.tran: “比赛结果怎样？”——“利兹队以1比0获胜。”

example.ex: The final election results will be announced on Friday.
example.tran: 选举的最终结果将在周五宣布。

value.def: A result is the number that you get when you do a calculation.

example.ex: They found their computers producing different results from exactly the same calculation.
example.tran: 他们发现他们的计算机进行完全相同的计算会得出不同的结果。

value.def: Your results are the marks or grades that you get for examinations you have taken.

example.tran: 凯特的考试成绩非常出色。

as 加强 + sault〔= sult〕跳 → 跳起来扣杀 → 进攻
de 离开 + sult 跳 + ory 有…性质的，属于…的，与…有关的 → 跳向四面八方 → 散漫的
ex 加强 + ult〔= sult〕跳 →〔高兴地〕跳起来 → 欢腾
in 使… + sult 跳 → 使跳到〔别人脸上〕→ 侮辱〔别人〕
